      "reviews": [
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Fantastic foundation!",
          "reviewText": "Amazing foundation! I have dealt with acne since I was a teenager, and I\u2019m now 30, still getting pimples. My whole life I have wanted a \u2018drugstore priced\u2019 foundation that provided full coverage that didn\u2019t sink into my fine lines or separate on my nose after a couple hours. I have used Maybelline Fit Me Matte + Poreless (which feels like wearing a mask with how much I have to apply for full coverage, and it sinks into my creases everywhere) and Fenty Pro Filter Foundation (love it, but hate the price). I think I\u2019ve found what I\u2019ve been looking for in this foundation! Full coverage almost immediately, my acne nearly disappeared, blends out into my neck well, melded right with my pores to give me a blurred look without applying ANY skin primer for extra \u2018grip\u2019. I just put on my moisturizer, covered my acne up with concealer and went in with this foundation. The pictures are covering up 10+ pimples, new and healing, flawlessly without a picture filter or anything! I couldn\u2019t believe it. And 10 hours later (thumbs up photo), it is still holding up perfectly! I don\u2019t feel greasy like I\u2019m wearing a liquid mask, my skin still looks great and my pores and lines are still practically invisible. I love that it\u2019s a pump bottle so I don\u2019t have to dump the foundation out onto the back of my hand and compromise the rest of what\u2019s in the bottle with bacteria. A little foundation went SO far, I think I used a quarter of what I usually would with Maybelline Fit Me foundation. So long as this foundation exists, I will not be going back!",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2026",
          "customer": "Randi",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AEYFPVCCZ4T66GIIUZSWB2KYFGMA",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "150 Buff",
            "size": "1 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "19 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Drugstore foundation that actually performs like high-end",
          "reviewText": "I\u2019ve tried a LOT of drugstore foundations and this one honestly competes with higher-end brands. The coverage is medium to full but still looks natural on the skin and not cakey. I have normal to slightly dry skin and this goes on really smooth, especially if I moisturize first. It blends easily with a sponge or brush and doesn\u2019t cling to dry patches like some foundations do. What impressed me the most is how long it lasts. I can wear this all day (work and errands) and it still looks good without breaking apart or getting patchy. It claims up to 24-hour wear, and while I haven\u2019t worn it that long, it definitely holds up through a full day. The finish is natural \u2014 not too matte and not too dewy \u2014 which I like because it doesn\u2019t look heavy in person. The SPF 20 is a nice bonus too. Shade 150 Buff is a good match for light to light-medium skin tones, but I would double-check undertones if you\u2019re unsure. Only small downside is it can transfer a little if you don\u2019t set it, but with a light powder it stays put. Overall, for the price, this is one of the best foundations I\u2019ve used and I\u2019ll definitely keep repurchasing.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on March 17, 2026",
